<item>
            <title>[SPARK-13002] Mesos scheduler backend does not follow the property spark.dynamicAllocation.initialExecutors</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-13002</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When starting a Spark job on a Mesos cluster, all available cores are reserved (up to &lt;tt&gt;spark.cores.max&lt;/tt&gt;), creating one executor per Mesos node, and as many executors as needed.&lt;br/&gt;
This is the case even when dynamic allocation is enabled.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When dynamic allocation is enabled, the number of executor launched at startup should be limited to the value of &lt;tt&gt;spark.dynamicAllocation.initialExecutors&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Mesos scheduler backend already follows the value computed by the &lt;tt&gt;ExecutorAllocationManager&lt;/tt&gt; for the number of executors that should be up and running. Expect at startup, when it just creates all the executors it can.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
